{
  "texts": [
    "74 There exists an extensive computer science and engineering literature on safety assurance and risk management in human-machine interaction already, which is largely ignored in the policy debate about AI regulation and AI liability.",
    "For surveys of these literature see e.g.",
    "Bozhinoski et al. (2019); Bi et al.",
    "(2021); Guiochet and Waeselynck (2017); Zacharaki et al. (2020); Veitch and Alsos (2022); and Villani et al.",
    "75 Safety considerations that account for possible misuse may play a key role in the design: more specifically, the software engineering process for autonomous robots may be safety oriented."
  ]
}